npm installations: npm install -g Typescript [**To install globally]
for converting .ts file to .js file : tsc filename.tsc
for checking npm is correctly installed or not: npm -v
For installing node js: nodejs.org
tsconfig.json file creation: tsc -- init
for creation of package.json : npm init
to create node_module or inside it system.js consist: npm install systemjs@0.19.36
to check node module : npm i systemjs
get the version of typescript : tsc -v 

*node package manager
when compilation successfull then .js file is created.then we can run it through html.